<subSubSection pageId="43" pageNumber="44" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="43.[151,1437,153,503]" pageId="43" pageNumber="44">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,171,153,179]" pageId="43" pageNumber="44">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[171,257,159,176]" pageId="43" pageNumber="44">REMARKS</emphasis>
</emphasis>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[257,264,153,179]" pageId="43" pageNumber="44">.</emphasis>
The species is medium sized (body length 
<quantity box="[749,866,153,179]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.25" metricValueMax="3.4" metricValueMin="3.1" pageId="43" pageNumber="44" unit="mm" value="32.5" valueMax="34.0" valueMin="31.0">31-34 mm</quantity>
) with a tawny and piceous body, the head pronotal collar mesothorax and posterior abdomen can be green in fresher specimens. The bright green basal area of the fore wings and bright red on the basal area of the hind wings make the species very easy to identify.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="43" pageNumber="44" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="43.[151,1437,153,503]" pageId="43" pageNumber="44">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,219,261,287]" pageId="43" pageNumber="44">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[219,350,267,284]" pageId="43" pageNumber="44">DISTRIBUTION</emphasis>
</emphasis>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[350,357,261,287]" pageId="43" pageNumber="44">.</emphasis>
The species has been recorded from 
<collectingCountry box="[784,855,261,287]" name="Brazil" pageId="43" pageNumber="44">Brazil</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[868,963,261,287]" name="Ecuador" pageId="43" pageNumber="44">Ecuador</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[976,1146,261,287]" name="French Guiana" pageId="43" pageNumber="44">French Guiana</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[1159,1251,261,287]" name="Panama" pageId="43" pageNumber="44">Panama</collectingCountry>
, and 
<collectingCountry box="[1312,1363,261,287]" name="Peru" pageId="43" pageNumber="44">Peru</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Metcalf, Z. P." pageId="43" pageNumber="44" pagination="1 - 585" refId="ref106666" refString="Metcalf, Z. P. (1963 a) General catalogue of the Homoptera, Fascicle VIII. Cicadoidea. Part 1. Cicadidae. Section I. Tibiceninae. North Carolina State College Contribution, 1502, i-vii + 1 - 585." type="journal article" year="1963">Metcalf 1963a</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Sanborn, A. F." box="[283,454,297,323]" pageId="43" pageNumber="44" pagination="377 - 418" refId="ref107675" refString="Sanborn, A. F. (2011 a) Checklist of the cicadas of French Guiana including new records and the description of nine new species (Insecta, Hemiptera, Cicadoidea, Cicadidae). Zoosystema, 33, 377 - 418. https: // doi. org / 10.5252 / z 2011 n 3 a 6" type="journal article" year="2011">Sanborn 2011a</bibRefCitation>
; 2013; 2018b). 
<bibRefCitation author="Jacobi, A." box="[629,776,297,323]" pageId="43" pageNumber="44" pagination="1 - 28" refId="ref105512" refString="Jacobi, A. (1907) Homoptera Andina. Die Zikaden des kordillerengebietes von Sudamerika nach systematik und Verbreitung. I. Cicadidae. Abhandlungen und Berichte des Koniglichen Zoologischen und Anthropologisch-Enthnographischen Museums zu Dresden, 11, 1 - 28. https: // doi. org / 10.1080 / 00222930709487386" type="journal article" year="1907">Jacobi (1907</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Jacobi, A." box="[788,845,296,323]" pageId="43" pageNumber="44" pagination="89 - 92" refId="ref105565" refString="Jacobi, A. (1951) Die Singzikaden. Titschack, Beitrage zur Fauna Perus, 2, 89 - 92." type="journal article" year="1951">1951</bibRefCitation>
) reported the species from Chanchamayo. The range was recently reduced when 
<collectingCountry box="[460,571,333,359]" name="Argentina" pageId="43" pageNumber="44">Argentina</collectingCountry>
and 
<collectingCountry box="[626,708,333,359]" name="Bolivia" pageId="43" pageNumber="44">Bolivia</collectingCountry>
were excluded from the distribution of the species correcting the misinterpretation (
<bibRefCitation author="Metcalf, Z. P." box="[358,525,369,396]" pageId="43" pageNumber="44" pagination="1 - 585" refId="ref106666" refString="Metcalf, Z. P. (1963 a) General catalogue of the Homoptera, Fascicle VIII. Cicadoidea. Part 1. Cicadidae. Section I. Tibiceninae. North Carolina State College Contribution, 1502, i-vii + 1 - 585." type="journal article" year="1963">Metcalf 1963a</bibRefCitation>
) of the original resource (
<bibRefCitation author="Sanborn, A. F." box="[819,997,369,396]" pageId="43" pageNumber="44" pagination="1 - 104" refId="ref108562" refString="Sanborn, A. F. (2019 b) The cicadas (Hemiptera: Cicadidae) of Bolivia including the descriptions of fifteen new species, the resurrection of one genus and two species, seven new combinations, six new synonymies, and twenty-eight new records. Zootaxa, 4655 (1), 1 - 104. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 4655.1.1" type="journal article" year="2019">Sanborn 2019b</bibRefCitation>
). The distribution in 
<collectingCountry box="[1234,1285,369,395]" name="Peru" pageId="43" pageNumber="44">Peru</collectingCountry>
supports this action as the records are from the middle of 
<collectingCountry box="[647,701,405,431]" name="Peru" pageId="43" pageNumber="44">Peru</collectingCountry>
, some 
<quantity box="[778,863,405,431]" metricMagnitude="5" metricUnit="m" metricValue="9.0" pageId="43" pageNumber="44" unit="km" value="900.0">900 km</quantity>
from the Bolivian border.
</paragraph>
